<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-563-109  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 563 109.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 4 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer Sciences gets $15.3 million army design contract.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Sciences Corp. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    CSC.andO;Topic:     Defense ContractsUnited States. ArmyMilitaryCommunications Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COMPUTER SCIENCES GETS $15.3 MILLION ARMY DESIGN CONTRACT FALLS CHURCH,VIRGINIA, U.S.A., 1990 OCT 4 (NB) -- Computer Sciences Corp. (CSC) has beenawarded a $15.3 million contract to develop and demonstrate its version of areserve component automation system (RCAS).andP;  The award is the first phase ofa three-phase competitive run-off for a contract with a potential value of $1billion.andM;RCAS is a system intended to enable the rapid mobilization of the ArmyNational Guard and Army Reserve in response to national emergencies and toalso serve the peacetime functions of these organizations.andP;  The project hasbeen referred to by government sources as being of high importance as theArmy adjusts its active manpower downward to fit lower budgets.andM;CSC heads one of two teams competing for the contract.andP;  Team members areAmerican Management Systems Inc. and Systems Research and Applications Corp.,andO;both of Arlington, VA., and Data General Corp. of Westboro, MA.andP;  The totalprogram calls for developing the system design and necessary custom software,furnishing the commercial hardware and software required, and deploying thecomplete information system to some 5,000 sites.andM;In the first phase, lasting approximately a year, the teams will develop anddemonstrate their system designs.andP;  In phase two, the Army expects to selectone prime contractor to develop and field the critical mobilization andlogistics elements of RCAS to all the sites over a three-year period.andP;  In thelast phase, spanning eight years, that contractor will expand RCAS with anumber of additional administrative functions.andP;  CSC estimates the value ofthe program at about $1 billion over the 12-year period.andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19901001/Press Contact: Jim Furlong,Computer Sciences, 213-615-0311)</TEXT></DOC>